BFS Word Ladder Solver Project Report
1. Introduction
This project implements the Breadth-First Search (BFS) algorithm to solve the Word Ladder problem. It finds the shortest transformation sequence from a start word to an end word by changing one letter at a time.
2. Objectives
- To understand BFS algorithm
- To apply BFS in solving real-world problems
- To build an efficient word transformation system
3. Methodology
The project uses BFS to explore all possible word transformations level-by-level. Each word is treated as a node, and edges exist between words that differ by one letter.
4. Algorithm
1. Start with initial word
2. Generate all valid one-letter transformations
3. Add them to queue
4. Repeat until target word is found
5. Return shortest path
5. Technologies Used
Python, BFS algorithm, text dataset
6. Output
The system outputs the shortest transformation path and number of steps required.
7. Applications
Spell checking, NLP, word games, AI search problems
8. Conclusion
This project demonstrates how BFS can be effectively used to find shortest paths in problems like Word Ladder.
